    return 1;                      // table not full -> usable, NO bound check
r = *(a1+0x2020);
if (r != 0 && *(r+0x18) != 0)
    return 1;                      // result marker set -> usable, NO bound check
if (a2 != 0) return a3 <= *(a1+0x2010);   // arg2 bound
else         return a3 <= *(a1+0x2018);   // non-arg2 bound (only reached when full AND marker clear)
```

Corrected routine (QkIsOrdinalUseableNew; unconditional in patched):
```
if (a3 <= 0x62) return 1;
if (*(a1+0x1FE8) == *(a1+0x1FEC)) return 0;
if (a2 == 0) {                              // NON-ARG2: always bound-checked
    if (a3 > *(a1+0x48) || a3 > *(a1+0x2008))
        return a3 <= *(a1+0x2018);
    return 0;
}
if (*(a1+0x2038) < *(a1+0x2030)) return 1;  // ARG2 path: unchanged
r = *(a1+0x2020);
if (r != 0 && *(r+0x18) != 0) return 1;
return a3 <= *(a1+0x2010);
```

The difference is confined to the non-arg2 path: the OLD routine routes it through the shared table path and returns 1 on the not-full / marker edges without checking 0x2018; the corrected routine always compares a3 <= *(a1+0x2018) there. The arg2 path is identical in both.

